## Steps of the walkthrough

The walkthrough is designed to be traversed sequentially:

 - a description of [the data](data.md)

 - step 0: [preparatory steps](prep.md) required to set up the walkthrough

 - step 1: [validate and consistently reformat](p1/index.md) input files

 - step 2: [signal-level quality control (QC)](p2/index.md)

 - step 3: [staging/annotation QC](p3/index.md)

 - step 4: [cleaning and interpolation](p4/index.md) to make an analysis-ready EEG dataset

 - step 5: [analyses to quantify individual differences in the sleep EEG](p5/index.md) as described above

Over time, we'll be adding a series of more advanced/in-depth sections under the [step 6: next steps](p6/index.md) page.

